              <span id="reviewTextContainer51265181" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer9607721758249197872">Very clearly written - just like our history papers were in college. Each chapter tackles a part of the subject so you can put the book down and pick it up over a long period of time and not be lost.<br/><br/>Faust debunks the romantic belief lots of us have that the majority of Southern women supported the war effort gladly. I liked that there was no judgment placed by the author on ladies&apos; behavior during the war but the portrait did end up being not very flattering.</span>
  <span id="freeText9607721758249197872" style="display:none">Very clearly written - just like our history papers were in college. Each chapter tackles a part of the subject so you can put the book down and pick it up over a long period of time and not be lost.<br /><br />Faust debunks the romantic belief lots of us have that the majority of Southern women supported the war effort gladly. I liked that there was no judgment placed by the author on ladies' behavior during the war but the portrait did end up being not very flattering.</span>
