<div id="review_2849684056" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/2849684056" />
    <a title="E B" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/18042642-e-b"><img alt="E B" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1362416667p2/18042642.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/2849684056?book_show_action=true">Jun 19, 2019</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="E B" class="user" itemprop="url" name="E B" href="/user/show/18042642-e-b">E B</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer2849684056" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer3664376324357435485">This book gives an idea of what the home-front of the Southern side of the American Civil War was like for those who didn&apos;t head into battle. The home-front in the south was largely female and many found themselves forced to take on roles only their male counterparts had ever partaken. This must have been especially hard for the wealthy elite as their way of life was turned upside-down.</span>
  <span id="freeText3664376324357435485" style="display:none">This book gives an idea of what the home-front of the Southern side of the American Civil War was like for those who didn't head into battle. The home-front in the south was largely female and many found themselves forced to take on roles only their male counterparts had ever partaken. This must have been especially hard for the wealthy elite as their way of life was turned upside-down.</span>
